course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{2}. Trim and thinly slice
@Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a 5- to 6-quart #heavy-bottomed pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add onion, scallion whites, and @Garlic Powder{2}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once aromatics are softened, add @Ground Turkey{20%ounce} and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}
to #pot{}. Cook, breaking meat up into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes}.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

Add @Flour{2%tablespoon} and stir to combine.

Stir @Chicken Stock Concentrate{4}, half the @Green Salsa{14.12%ounce}, and @Water{2%cups}
(4 cups for 8 servings) into pot; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Bring to a boil,
then reduce heat to medium. Simmer until thickened, ~{7%minutes}.

Stir in @Cannellini Beans{2} and their liquid. Simmer until flavors are combined,
~{3-4%minutes} more.

Taste and season chili with salt and pepper.

Divide chili between bowls. Top with @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}, scallion greens,
and remaining salsa. Serve.